
🔥 == vs ===: What's the Difference?
Comparison	       Name	          Type Conversion	  Example	                 Result
==	          Loose Equality	     ✅ Yes	      "5" == 5→ string to number	true
===	          Strict Equality	     ❌ No	      "5" === 5	                    false

0 == false        // true
"" == false       // true
null == undefined // true
"0" == 0          // true

Template literals are a modern way (ES6 feature) to create strings in JavaScript using backticks (`), not single quotes (') or double quotes (").